Tell Him , Judea's Temple is no more , Upon whose Splendour , Thousands heretofore Spent the astonished Hours , forgetful to Adore : Tell him , into the Earth again is hurled , That most stupendious Wonder of the World , Justly presiding over the boasted Seven , By humane Art and Industry designed , This ! the rich Draught of the Immortal Mind , The Architect of Heaven
